These are names I found whilst working on #1171 around where ServerWorld works with the CsvWriter.


Changed the exportX methods to dumpX methods since that is the terminology used elsewhere, and fits with what Mojang seems to be doing.


BakedQuad was missing mappings that I'm sure were mapped in 1.15, but weren't in this version


Some names as per Mojang:


ServerChunkManager
method_21694 -> getPendingTasks
ServerTickScheduler
method_20825  -> getTicks
writer.write(String.format("entities: %d\n", this.entitiesById.size()));
writer.write(String.format("block_entities: %d\n", this.field_9231.size()));
writer.write(String.format("block_ticks: %d\n", this.method_14196().getTicks()));
writer.write(String.format("fluid_ticks: %d\n", this.method_14179().getTicks()));
writer.write("distance_manager: " + lv.getTicketManager().getDebugString() + "\n");
writer.write(String.format("pending_tasks: %d\n", this.method_14178().getPendingTasks()));

method_14196, method_14179, method_14178 don't show up as mappable in Enigma, so I couldn't confirm whether they have names or not.
That's about it, really.

